commitResults.messageBody:
Add ability to mark and unmark tasks as done, as per Duke level 3
requirements

Tasks are of 3 specific types as mentioned in subject header.
Add functionality in Duke to handle the addition of these 3 types of
tasks, as per level 4 requirements.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to save tasks to hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Currenly, Tasks are not preserved across sessions of Duke.

To preserve state across sessions of Duke, the taskList has to be
written to memory.

Now, any commands that modify the list of tasks will be written to the hard
disk.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Date/Time instead of String for dates
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the dates for `Deadline` and `Event` are stored as strings.

We should aim to represent this as a DateTime class instead of a String.

This change stores dates and time as `java.time.LocalDate` and `java.time.LocalTime` objects respectively.

After merging level-7 and level-8 to master, the features were
incompatible with each other.

This commit ensures these two features are compatible with each other.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Ui class to deal with interaction with user.
Refactor list of tasks into separate class
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, an `ArrayList<Task>` was used to contain the list of tasks.
Methods were then declared to manipulate the items in `ArrayList`

However, this is not good practice of encapsulation.

Thus, behaviour involving manipulating the list of tasks and
the `ArrayList<Task>` instance have been refactored into their separate
class.

Two packages have been created: `duke` and `duke.task`. The latter
consists of `Task.java` and its subclasses. The former contains all
other `.java` file.
